A 30-YEAR-OLD man is fighting for his life in hospital after he was attacked by angry residents.The man from H section in Umlazi, KZN, was beaten after he was accused of killing his girlfriend on 29 December.The 23-year-old woman from J section in Umlazi, was allegedly shot and stabbed, then burnt before her body was dumped in the bushes just a few metres from the man&rsquo;s house. Her body was found on Tuesday. The dead woman&rsquo;s dad (61) told Daily Sun: &ldquo;When I woke up last Thursday, my daughter was not at home, and nobody knew where she had gone to. And when we could not reach her on her cellphone, we reported the matter to the police.&ldquo;We then conducted our own search with relatives,&rdquo; he said. &ldquo;We drove to Mthatha in the Eastern Cape and Zululand to see different sangomas. One of them told us that she was still alive and demanded money to bring her back.&rdquo;The dad added that on Tuesday, his daughters went to search the boyfriend&rsquo;s house and found bloodstains.They followed the stains into the bush and found her belt and then her badly burnt body.The belt was used to identify her.&ldquo;She was allegedly picked up by the boyfriend on the night she went missing,&rdquo; he said.After the body was discovered, angry residents burned down the boyfriend&rsquo;s house while others traced him to C section where they attacked him.In a separate incident in H section, a body of a 10-year-old child was found dumped near a school on Tuesday. Nomfundo Tsotetsi went missing two weeks ago when she was sent to buy airtime at a spaza shop. Police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said Umlazi police were investigating two cases of murder.